Put a #pot{} of water on high heat (this will be for the rice). Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Line a #baking tray{} with #parchment paper{}. Slice the @butternut squash{1} in half lengthways and scoop out the seeds. Cut the slimmer top part off and separate from the bulbous bottom (no need to peel!). Chop each piece into six wedges.

Pop the wedges onto the baking tray. Season with @salt{} and drizzle on a glug of @oil{}. Toss and then roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{30%minutes}. Turn halfway. When the pot of water comes to the boil add the @brown basmati rice{300%g} with a pinch of @salt{} and cook for ~{25%minutes} uncovered.

Heat a #casserole pan{} over medium heat and add a splash of @oil{}. Add the @Toulouse sausages{8} and cook for ~{12-15%minutes} turning frequently until they are browned all over and cooked through.

> The sausage is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root. Peel and then slice into thin half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}. Remove the top and bottom of the @courgette{1}. Cut it lengthways into four long strips and then chop each strip into 1cm chunks. Pull the @tarragon{1} leaves off their stalks. Discard the stalks and roughly chop the leaves.

When your sausages are cooked remove them from the pan and keep to one side. Drain off any excess oil and return it to medium heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{2} and onion to the pan for ~{5%minutes} until your pancetta has browned and your onion has softened. Then add your courgette and cook for another ~{2%minutes}.

Next, add your garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} more and then add the @chicken stock pot{1}. Add the @water{250%ml} to the pan and bring to the boil. Stir and then reduce the heat to low and simmer for ~{7-10%minutes}.

Slice your sausages into bite-sized pieces and return them to the pan along with the @baby spinach{1}. Stir in half the @wholegrain mustard{1} and the @crème fraîche{1}. Cook until your sauce is bubbling, and your courgette is soft. Taste your sauce and add more mustard if necessary and stir in your tarragon leaves.

Drain your rice into a #colander{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} to taste. Spoon a helping of rice and your sausage casserole onto each #plate{}. Pop your butternut wedges on top and tuck in!